column5: Here I sit looking out my window watching these lake effect squalls rolling in off L Ontario this morning.
There are here now in Orangeville, can`t see the end of my driveway!
Funny , here i sit just north of Barrie , seconds ago it was like a cloud burst , full out white out , can't see ten feet ahead
here i sit in keswick an few flakes an the sun already melted it. Sweet! flip
ok i gotta change my last post, its 12;20 an high winds an white out conditions. Man it sure changed FAST. flip
From London to Kingston to Sudbury its giving it , kind of like the best old fashion March we've had in a while .
Snowing hard over this way too but the sunny warm weather that's coming in a couple days will take care of it.
Lindsay was clear, Sturgeon Lake getting the biggest blizzard we've seen all winter!
Was an interesting drive this morning down to the Big Smoke!
Same here. Clear when I left Sturgeon Lake at 0700, then huge flakes on Hwy 35, then total whiteouts on 401.
hey wiskey, Sunday over across lake X (we'll drive around) +14 light winds if you are interested, give me a call.
